This will be a randomized study with the primary objective of assessing the impact of withholding versus encouraging breastfeeding on the immunogenicity of Rotarix(R) in infants.

 Enrolled subjects will all be administered Rotarix(R), at ages 6 to 7 weeks, and at10 -14 weeks.

 The subjects will be randomized into one of the two study arms.

 In one of the group caregivers will be advised to breastfeed immediately prior to and after each dose of the vaccine while in the other group caregivers will be advised to withhold breastfeeding for 30 minutes before and after each dose of the vaccine.

